Lasseters International to Dispose of Australian Assets for $82 Million; Shares Soar 36%12:30 AM EDT  04/20/2021 (MT Newswires) -- Integrated resort operator Lasseters International (SGX:5EL) plans to dispose of its Australian assets and business for A$105 million ($81.9 million) to companies under the Australian integrated development and hospitality group  Iris Capital  according to a Monday bourse disclosure.The company's subsidiary Ford Dynasty on Monday signed an agreement with Alice Springs Casino Property and Alice Springs Casino Operation for the disposal of the freehold land and buildings  improvements of Ford Dynasty  and the disposal of its casino hotel and convention center business  as well as non-real property business assets.Under the agreement  Ford Dynasty will retain ownership of the Lasseters brand and has granted Alice Springs Casino Operation an exclusive  royalty-free license to use the Lasseters brand in Australia  the filing said.Lasseters International said the disposal is in the group's best interests as it provides a good opportunity for the group to unlock the value of the assets.Another unit  Lasseters Health Club  agreed to dispose of its business and assets to Alice Springs Casino Operation  it said.The company plans to use the proceeds from the disposal to pay bank loans  boost working capital and fund investments in the property management and development business.Lasseters International's shares were up 39% recently.Price (SGD): S$0.05  Change: S$0.02  Percent Change: +38.46%
